      <originalsloc id="aspace_74d95159034f1920afe22a98a19afffb">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>Previously: Misc. Film # 866 
  
This film is not connected to an MS or RU</p>
         <p>Restriction is on Reproduction Only:</p>
         <p>Originals are in the Rhodes House Library, Bodleian Library, Oxford University, Oxford, England.    An entire reproduction of this microfilm may be made only with the permission of Moore Crossey, African Collection, Yale University Library.</p>
         <p>Biographical/Historical note: Hubert Frank Mathews was born in 1885. He studied anthropology and worked in Nigeria as a political officer in the north. Following further study in anthropology at Oxford, he became an anthropological officer for the Southern Provinces, Nigeria. Mathews died in 1964.    Summary: The papers consist of letters sent by Hubert Frank Mathews to his parents describing his work in Nigeria. Also included are official correspondence and reports, manuscripts of writings, notes, and printed matter. These papers are MSS Afr. S.783 in the Bodleian Library, Oxford, England.</p>
         <p>Indexes/Finding aids: Published guide available in Microform Reference.</p>  
      </originalsloc>
